children.text: The area above the bath has not been waterproofed 150mm high in accordance with the Building Code of Australia (BCA) and relevant Australian Standard AS 3740 to prevent water leaks into the structure that could cause damage.
Part 3.8.1.2 of the Building Code of Australia (NCC/BCA) - Wet Areas, states that;
‘Building elements in wet areas within a building must-
be waterproof or water resistant in accordance with Table 3.8.1.1; and
Table 3.8.1.1 in the NCC/BCA shows that the wall over the bath must be waterproofed to 150mm high;
The builder must install waterproofing to 150mm high around the bath as required by the NCC’s Building Code of Australia and Australian Standard AS 3740.
